org.gbif.registry.ws.model

Class LegacyDataset

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.api.model.registry.Dataset
      • org.gbif.registry.ws.model.LegacyDataset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.gbif.api.model.registry.Commentable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Contactable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Endpointable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Identifiable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.LenientEquals<org.gbif.api.model.registry.Dataset>, org.gbif.api.model.registry.MachineTaggable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.NetworkEntity, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Taggable

    public class LegacyDataset
extends org.gbif.api.model.registry.Dataset
    Class used to create or update a Dataset for legacy (GBRDS/IPT) API. Previously known as a Resource in the GBRDS. A set of HTTP Form parameters coming from a POST request are injected.
    Its fields are injected using the @FormParam. It is assumed the following parameters exist in the HTTP request: 'organisationKey', 'name', 'description', 'primaryContactName', 'primaryContactEmail', 'primaryContactType', 'serviceTypes', 'serviceURLs', 'homepageURL', 'primaryContactPhone', 'logoURL', and 'primaryContactAddress'.
    JAXB annotations allow the class to be converted into an XML document, that gets included in the Response following a successful registration or update. @XmlElement is used to specify element names that consumers of legacy services expect to find.
